<h1><a name="a-namea-nametesting-utf-8-character-handling"></a><a name="a-nametesting-utf-8-character-handling"></a><a name="testing-utf-8-character-handling"></a>Testing UTF-8 Character Handling</h1>

This template contains various UTF-8 characters to test encoding handling:

<h2><a name="a-namea-namesmart-quotes-and-punctuation"></a><a name="a-namesmart-quotes-and-punctuation"></a><a name="smart-quotes-and-punctuation"></a>Smart Quotes and Punctuation</h2>

- "Smart double quotes" and 'smart single quotes'
- Em dashes—like this—and en dashes–like this
- Ellipsis… and other fancy punctuation

<h2><a name="a-namea-nameaccented-characters"></a><a name="a-nameaccented-characters"></a><a name="accented-characters"></a>Accented Characters</h2>

- Café, naïve, résumé, déjà vu
- Über, Zürich, Köln
- São Paulo, François, Łódź

<h2><a name="a-namea-namespecial-symbols"></a><a name="a-namespecial-symbols"></a><a name="special-symbols"></a>Special Symbols</h2>

- © Copyright symbol
- ® Registered trademark
- € Euro sign
- £ Pound sign
- ¥ Yen sign
- ™ Trademark
- • Bullet point

<h2><a name="a-namea-namehtml-entities-mixed-with-utf-8"></a><a name="a-namehtml-entities-mixed-with-utf-8"></a><a name="html-entities-mixed-with-utf-8"></a>HTML Entities Mixed with UTF-8</h2>

This should handle &ldquo;HTML entities&rdquo; alongside "UTF-8 smart quotes".

The template should process all of these correctly without warnings.

[% END %]
